            End of Twitter post  by @BBCr4today
        
    

Speaking to John Humphrys on the Today programme on Radio 4, Mr Hedges said being in a cell was "was lonely and isolating".He said he was given a "cocktail" of medication to treat his depression and anxiety.He said: "There was no natural light - I wasn't allowed to do anything to distract myself. My mental health was deteriorating. "I was handcuffed and blindfolded. I had to stand all day in ankle cuffs."
